# Rasm Vectors

Read `libs/csharp/Rasm/AGENTS.md`, `docs/external-libs/mathnet`, and package truth before numerical edits.

## Ownership

- `Vectors/` owns vector intent, direction, support-space projection, fields, rays, spans, signed axes, relation logic, mesh-aware field algebra, spectral filters, and cloud metrics.
- `Domain/` owns shared validity, tolerance, statistics, geometry identity, and projection carriers.

## Rules

- Route consumer intent through `VectorIntent.Project<TOut>` and existing vector owners before adding entrypoints.
- Keep DEC, spectral filters, Laplacian cache, sparse factorization, field algebra, and mesh/cloud dispatch centralized.
- Use MathNet and approved sparse/numeric libraries where they provide real numerical value.
- Preserve independent or bridge-backed oracles for geometry, spectral, field, and cloud changes.
- Do not duplicate `Analysis` or `Domain` validation locally.

## Validation

Run `bash scripts/check-cs.sh check`, `bash scripts/test.sh`, and vector bridge scenarios when native Rhino/GH evidence changes.
